			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, let me start this by saying that all the bard creation guides I have read and all the great advice I have gotten from forums like this one says basically not to waste any of your training points by putting them in CHA. Pretty much all I have seen says to create a great bard you should put your training points mainly into STM and AGI with every fourth one or so going into STR and to just look for items to buff your DEX up.
<br />

<br />
That being said last night I was grouping with a guy who said he was a beta tester and we got to talking about bards. He said he liked bards cause of all the stuff they could do, including healing. I told him that our heal wasn't so good and currently mine only did 16 a tick. So then he tells me I must not be putting any points into CHA (which is correct I haven't, my CHA is 70 I think). I proceed to tell him what I have read here and other places that CHA does not help bards too much because CHA only helps the Lull/Soothe songs.
<br />
He tells me that I am flat out wrong and that if I increase my CHA that my heal song will be better.
<br />

<br />
So I about hit the floor. Then he goes on to tell me that not only is the Heal song based on CHA but that ALL bard songs are CHA based. That leaves me with some questions that I hope some of you high lvl bards (like Seremorn or Quilyn) can answer. 
<br />

<br />
#1. Is this true? Are all bard songs CHA based?
<br />

<br />
#2. If it is true then how high can you get the bard heal up to with CHA increases? I doubt it can be in the 100's but can it be like 50 or 60 a tick if your CHA is high enough?
<br />

<br />
#3. What kind of CHA score should I be looking for at lvl 35-40 if I want to be more effective with my songs?
<br />

<br />
Thanks for the help!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
