				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hmmm. I definetely don't think charisma will do any good for the bard. Buff spells will only buff as much as they have been intended to do. For example, Anthem of Triumph adds like 62 (im not exactly sure, but its around 60) to srtength and dexterity. There is no way to increase this. The only thing that charisma might increase is how long the spell lasts.  The same applies to the ac buff and ac debuff. I hope you don't  waste training points on charisma when you could be putting them into strength, stamina, or dexterity. Personally, I am focusing on strength, and dexterity. I can outdamage a lvl 50 ranger, and I chain cast the lvl 40 and 49 power regen songs, so i never run out of mana. Although I cant take quite as much of a hit as other bards that focused more on sta and agi, i can do way more damage, while using the same buffs. Not to say that that beta tester was wrong, he may have been correct about the beta versions, but there have been many changes since beta. it is possible that charisma made a difference in beta, but doesnt anymore.  And as for higher charisma making your health regen tick higher, thats what healers are for <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> I would appreciate any comments or criticisms on my ideas. please post your thoughts.
<br />

<br />
Melanie
