				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> The only thing that charisma might increase is how long the spell lasts. The same applies to the ac buff and ac debuff. I hope you don't waste training points on charisma when you could be putting them into strength, stamina, or dexterity. 
<br />

<br />
And as for higher charisma making your health regen tick higher, thats what healers are for  I would appreciate any comments or criticisms on my ideas. please post your thoughts. 
<br />

<br />
Melanie 
