<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Well True, healing is what healers are for...sigh...
<br />

<br />
But there are and will be times when healers are hard to come by. Also very effective soloing. 
<br />

<br />
Being at L30 almost all my important stats are either base 100 or close to. The stats being Strenght,Stamina, Agility, Dex, and finally Charisma. With my buff Anthem of Drive both Strength and Dex are 200. Also Agility is 200 (with stats from armor, weapons ect..). My stamina is the only stat not buffed by armor except for my gloves. But I think I do ok in the Damage department. I am not to concerned with being an Uber Damage Dealer. If I did I could have stayed with my L35 Ranger or gone to another class all together.
<br />

<br />
I see myself as a true Support player. My belt is usually filled with Buffs, Debuffs, DoT, or maybe an extra melee attack. 
<br />

<br />
So in conclusion about my opinions in Charisma is it worth it. Prolly not if your already a higher level Bard. But if you are to start one from scratch I wouldn't ignore Charisma. I'm happy I can heal better than any Bard my level. With increased Charisma and levels who knows what the Bards Heals are capable. I think I will be the first to know. Stay tuned.....</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
